{
  "title": "ISic001377. Fragmentary Greek funerary inscription",
  "body": "<div id=\"editions\"><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag</div><div id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  <div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  <a id=\"al1-interpretive\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-text=\"ἐνθάδε\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"ἐνθάδε\">ἐνθάδ[ε</span>  <span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>] <br id=\"al2-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span><span data-text=\"ζησασ\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"ζάω\">ζησασ</span> [<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>] <br id=\"al3-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span><span data-text=\"ἔτη\" data-n=\"25\" data-lemma=\"ἔτος\">ἔτη</span>  <span data-text=\"ν\" data-n=\"30\" data-lemma=\"ν\"><span class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">ν</span></span>´ [<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>] <br id=\"al4-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">4</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>] ΥΤΟ[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>] </span></div>  <p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Victoria Fendel, Robert Crellin</div><div id=\"edition-interpretive-simple-lemmatized\">  <div class=\"textpart\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  <span data-text=\"ἐνθάδε\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"ἐνθάδε\">ἐνθάδε</span> [<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>] <span data-text=\"ζησασ\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"ζάω\">ζησασ</span> [<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>] <span data-text=\"ἔτη\" data-n=\"25\" data-lemma=\"ἔτος\">ἔτη</span>  <span data-text=\"ν\" data-n=\"30\" data-lemma=\"ν\">ν</span> [<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span> ] ΥΤΟ [<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>] </span></div>  <p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag</div><div id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\"><div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\"><a id=\"al1-diplomatic\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-text=\"ἐνθάδε\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"ἐνθάδε\">ΕΝΘΑΔ[.</span><span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]<br id=\"al2-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span><span data-text=\"ζησασ\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"ζάω\">ΖΗΣΑΣ</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]<br id=\"al3-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span><span data-text=\"ἔτη\" data-n=\"25\" data-lemma=\"ἔτος\">ΕΤΗ</span><span data-text=\"ν\" data-n=\"30\" data-lemma=\"ν\"><span class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">Ν</span></span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]<br id=\"al4-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">4</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]ΥΤΟ[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]</span></div><p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Victoria Fendel, Robert Crellin</div><div id=\"edition-diplomatic-simple-lemmatized\"><div class=\"textpart\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\"><span data-text=\"ἐνθάδε\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"ἐνθάδε\">ΕΝΘΑΔΕ</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]<span data-text=\"ζησασ\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"ζάω\">ΖΗΣΑΣ</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]<span data-text=\"ἔτη\" data-n=\"25\" data-lemma=\"ἔτος\">ΕΤΗ</span><span data-text=\"ν\" data-n=\"30\" data-lemma=\"ν\">Ν</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]ΥΤΟ[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]</span></div><p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div></div>  <div id=\"facsimile-images\"><h2>Facsimile Images</h2></div>  <div id=\"apparatus\"><h4>Apparatus criticus</h4><ul><li><span>  <span>Text after Amico and Kaibel</span>  </span>; </li><li><span class=\"1\">1: <span>Amico 1741: 274: ΕΝΘΑΚ</span>  </span><br></li><li><span class=\"3\">3: <span>Amico 1741: 274: ΕΤΗΝ; Amico 1741: 277: ΕΤΕΝ̅</span>  </span><br></li><li><span class=\"4\">4: <span>Amico 1741: 274: ΚΤΩ....; Kirchoff: [τελευτᾷ τῇ πρὸ -- Ὀ]κτω[βρίων]; Ferrua: [ὑπατίᾳ — —ο]υ τὸ[</span>  </span></li></ul></div>  <div id=\"translation\"><h2> translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\">  </p><p>  </p></div>  <div id=\"commentary\"><h2>commentary</h2>  <p>Amico presents the text in two different variants, without seemingly recognising that it is the same text. Ferrua suggests that the traces in line 4 would be compatible with a consular dating, such as for an imperial consul, as with Honorius in 404 CE, but obviously the actual date is speculative. Kirchoff in CIG offered a possible restoration of line 3-4 on the basic of Amico's alternative reading.</p>  </div>  <div id=\"bibliography\"><h2>bibliography</h2>  <ul><li> 36.0844 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796</a>  </li><li> Amico 1741 274, 277 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002186\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002186</a>  </li><li> Kirchhoff 1877 9500 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001249\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001249</a>  </li><li> Kaibel 1890 <a href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">558</a>  <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072</a>  </li><li> Ferrua 1982-1983 27 no.91 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001996\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001996</a>  </li></ul>  <ul><li></li></ul>  </div>  <div id=\"handnote\"> <p>lunate sigma and the use of a supraline on numeral recorded by Amico</p> Line 1    Interlineation line 1 to 2    </div><div id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. </div>",
